The paper deals with probabilistic rewriting systems and their operational properties, which are fundamental topics in theoretical computer science. The use of abstract tools and the investigation of normalizing strategies suggest a focus on logic and computation (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The study of uniqueness of the result and comparison of different rewrite sequences suggest a connection to theoretical computer science (cs.TCS) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the mention of probabilistic lambda-calculi and non-deterministic evaluation suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
